  <description type="morphology">Flowering stems creeping, 0.5–1.5 dm. Leaves opposite; blade obovate or orbiculate,
        1–3 cm, margins prominently glandular, coarsely crenate apically. Flowers: sepals deltate to
        lanceolate, 4–4.5 mm, apex subobtuse; petals erect basally, recurved at tips, white to pink,
        ovate, 8–11 mm, apex shortly mucronate. Carpels erect in fruit, connate
        basally.</description>
